		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Providence</placeName> the <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Jany 1854</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Leeser Esq</addressee><add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Sir I beg leave to inform you<lb/> that we have established a congregation here in<lb/> <placeName>Providence</placeName>.  The whole members met together last<lb/> <date>Sunday</date>&#44; and signed their names for supporting<lb/> the society with 50 cnt each every week&#44; and named<lb/> it &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41; Bene Israel.  They elected their officers&#44;<lb/> namely <persName>Mr Pareira</persName> President&#44; <persName>Mr. Frank</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr Stern</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>Mr Solomon</persName>&#44; and <persName>Mr Steinberg</persName> <sic>Comittee</sic>&#44; <persName>Mr.<lb/> Hirschhorn</persName> has been elected as Sec. and treasurer.<lb/>  They engaged me as their Minister&#44; and promised<lb/> me &#36;5.50 cnt weekly <sic>sallary</sic> without other income.<lb/>  They also promised me to have a hall ready<lb/> to perform and to deliver our Prayers to<lb/> our holy God&#44; <sic>befor</sic> &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41; and to fix every<lb/> thing in a suitable manner.  They bought already<lb/> a &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41;&#44; and are in undertaking of making around<lb/> a fence&#44; that is all I have to inform you<lb/> about it at present.  I hope I shall be<lb/> able to inform you more about it next<lb/> <del>week</del> month.  You will please send me the<lb/> Occident as soon as possible.</p>
				<p>I allow me to <del>signed</del> sign</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Joseph Spiro</persName></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>Author of the Occident or the</p>
				<p><sic>american</sic> <sic>Advocat</sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Paid</p>
		</body>
